08/01/2010
TIRANA, Albania -- Police in Gjirokastra seized 650kg of marijuana on Thursday (January 7th) in the village of Lazarat, just outside Gjirokastra. Police units moved in, acting on prior information that the delivery to the coastal south city of Saranda was going to take place early that morning. The suspects dumped the load and managed to escape in nearby villages amid bad weather conditions. (Start, Top Channel, Balkan Web, Telegrafi - 07/01/10)
